# Olympus Quality Standards

These rules are MANDATORY for every agent in the pipeline. They come from real production bugs found in testing. Every agent MUST follow them.

## CRITICAL BUG PREVENTION

### 1. Text Contrast — NEVER dark text on dark backgrounds

- ALL text on dark backgrounds MUST be readable: `text-foreground`, `text-white`, `text-zinc-100`, `text-zinc-200`, `text-zinc-300`, `text-zinc-400` — NEVER `text-zinc-600`, `text-zinc-700`, `text-zinc-800` on dark cards/backgrounds
- Labels and helper text: minimum `text-muted-foreground` (which resolves to a readable gray)
- Test: if you can't read the text against its background, it's wrong

### 2. Sidebar — MUST be h-screen, sticky, not page-height

Desktop sidebar:
```
w-64 sticky left-0 top-0 h-screen bg-background border-r border-border flex flex-col
```
- `h-screen` NOT `h-full` — sidebar must fill the viewport, not the page content
- `sticky` on desktop, `fixed` on mobile with overlay
- `flex flex-col` with `flex-1 overflow-y-auto` for nav scroll and `flex-shrink-0` for header/footer
- Navigation items go in the scrollable region, NOT as floating action buttons

Mobile sidebar:
```
fixed left-0 top-0 z-50 w-64 h-screen bg-background border-r border-border flex flex-col transform -translate-x-full transition-transform
```
Plus dark overlay: `fixed inset-0 bg-black/50 z-40`

### 3. Color Opacity Bug — NEVER stack opacity on custom HSL colors

This is the #1 Tailwind bug:
```
❌ WRONG: bg-primary/60  (if --primary already has alpha in its HSL)
❌ WRONG: bg-[hsl(var(--custom-color))]/50
✅ RIGHT: bg-primary (use the color as-is)
✅ RIGHT: bg-primary hover:bg-primary/90 (single opacity modifier, base has no alpha)
```

Rules:
- CSS variables for colors MUST be defined as `H S% L%` WITHOUT alpha (e.g. `--primary: 20 100% 50%`)
- Opacity modifiers like `/60` only work when the base HSL has NO built-in alpha
- If `--border` uses alpha like `44 6% 51% / 0.2`, do NOT add another `/` modifier on top
- When in doubt, use the semantic class directly: `bg-card`, `border-border`, `text-foreground`

### 4. Button Colors — NEVER leave white/unstyled buttons

- Primary actions: `bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90`
- Secondary: `bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground hover:bg-secondary/80`
- Destructive: `bg-destructive text-destructive-foreground`
- Ghost: `hover:bg-accent hover:text-accent-foreground`
- NEVER: bare `bg-white`, `text-black`, or unstyled buttons in a dark theme

### 5. Layout Shell — proper flex structure

```tsx
// Root
<div className="h-full w-full bg-background flex flex-col overflow-x-hidden">
  <div className="flex-1 flex min-w-0 overflow-x-hidden">
    {/* Sidebar (sticky h-screen) */}
    <Sidebar />
    {/* Main */}
    <div className="flex-1 flex flex-col min-w-0 overflow-x-hidden">
      <Header />
      <main className="flex-1 overflow-y-auto p-6">
        {content}
      </main>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

- `html, body, #root` must all have `height: 100%`
- `min-w-0` on flex children to prevent overflow
- `overflow-x-hidden` to prevent horizontal scroll

## DESIGN QUALITY STANDARDS

### 6. CSS Variables — use semantic tokens, not raw Tailwind colors

Define in index.css:
```css
.dark {
  --background: 0 0% 5%;        /* near black */
  --foreground: 0 0% 100%;      /* white */
  --card: 0 0% 7%;              /* slightly lighter */
  --card-foreground: 0 0% 100%;
  --muted: 0 0% 10%;
  --muted-foreground: 0 0% 60%;
  --border: 0 0% 15%;           /* NO ALPHA — use plain HSL */
  --input: 0 0% 12%;
  --primary: 20 100% 50%;       /* orange/amber */
  --primary-foreground: 0 0% 100%;
}
```

Use in components:
```
bg-background, bg-card, bg-muted, bg-primary
text-foreground, text-card-foreground, text-muted-foreground
border-border, border-input
```

### 7. Tables — desktop table + mobile card list (MANDATORY pattern)

Desktop (hidden on mobile):
```tsx
<div className="hidden lg:block">
  <table className="w-full">
    <thead>
      <tr className="border-b border-border bg-card/50">
        <th className="text-left py-3 px-4 text-sm font-medium text-muted-foreground">Column</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr className="border-b border-border hover:bg-accent/20 transition-colors h-16 cursor-pointer">
        <td className="py-2 px-4 text-sm text-foreground">Data</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>
```

Mobile (hidden on desktop):
```tsx
<div className="lg:hidden">
  <div className="divide-y divide-border">
    {items.map(item => (
      <div className="p-4 hover:bg-accent/20 transition-colors cursor-pointer">
        <div className="flex items-center justify-between">
          <div className="flex items-center gap-3">
            <img src={item.icon} className="w-8 h-8 rounded-full" />
            <div>
              <div className="text-foreground font-medium text-sm">{item.title}</div>
              <div className="text-xs text-muted-foreground">{item.subtitle}</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div className="text-right">
            <div className="text-foreground text-sm font-medium">{item.value}</div>
            <div className="text-xs text-muted-foreground">{item.meta}</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>
</div>
```

### 8. Modals — portal-based, proper mobile adaptation

- Use `createPortal(content, document.body)` for all modals
- Desktop: centered with `max-w-lg`, `rounded-2xl`
- Mobile: bottom sheet with `rounded-t-2xl`, slide from bottom animation
- ALWAYS lock body scroll when modal is open
- ALWAYS have close button AND backdrop click to dismiss

### 9. Currency/Asset Icons — use real images, not generic placeholders

For crypto icons:
- Use local SVGs: `/img/coins/bitcoin.svg`, `/img/coins/ethereum.svg`, `/img/coins/tether.svg` etc.
- Or use CoinGecko API: `https://api.coingecko.com/api/v3/coins/{id}?localization=false` → `image.small`
- Or use CryptoCompare: `https://cryptocompare.com/media/...`

For country flags:
- Use local SVGs from a flag pack (e.g. circle-flags)
- Or use Flagpedia CDN: `https://flagcdn.com/w40/{country-code}.png`

NEVER use a generic circle or Lucide icon as a crypto/currency symbol.

### 10. Empty States — EVERY list/table must have one

```tsx
{items.length === 0 && (
  <div className="flex flex-col items-center justify-center py-16 px-8">
    <div className="w-16 h-16 bg-muted/20 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
      <FileText className="w-8 h-8 text-muted-foreground" />
    </div>
    <h3 className="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground mb-2">Nenhum item encontrado</h3>
    <p className="text-muted-foreground text-center max-w-sm">Descrição do que fazer.</p>
  </div>
)}
```

### 11. Navigation — sidebar items are NAVIGATION, not action buttons

- Quick actions (deposit, convert, withdraw) go in the SIDEBAR as navigation items with their own pages, NOT as floating action buttons
- Each sidebar item navigates to a FULL PAGE view
- The sidebar organizes items by section: "Principal" (Home, Wallet), "Transações" (Deposit, Convert, Withdraw, Transfer), "Outros" (History, Settings, etc.)
- Footer items: Support, Profile, Logout

### 12. Screen Completeness Checklist

Every feature screen MUST have:
- [ ] Header with title and actions
- [ ] Main form/content area
- [ ] History/activity table below the main content (with desktop+mobile layouts)
- [ ] Empty state for the history table
- [ ] Loading state (skeleton or spinner)
- [ ] Error state with retry
- [ ] Status badges using semantic colors (green=success, yellow=pending, red=error/cancelled)
- [ ] Real-looking mock data (dates, amounts, names — not "lorem ipsum")

### 13. Form Quality

- Labels ALWAYS visible (not only placeholder)
- Validation messages below fields in `text-destructive` / `text-red-500`
- Primary submit button uses `bg-primary text-primary-foreground`
- Submit button shows loading state (spinner + disabled)
- "Available balance" text when relevant: `text-muted-foreground`
- Currency amount inputs: large font, right-aligned or centered, with currency symbol

### 14. Success/Completion Screens

After a major action (deposit, withdraw, convert):
- Full-screen or large modal with success/error icon
- Green circle with checkmark for success, red circle with X for error
- Summary card with all transaction details
- "Download Receipt" secondary button
- "Back to [feature]" primary button
- Animate in with `animate-in fade-in`
